{"rawJson":null,"m_plot":"Set in Glasgow, the film centers around 50-year-old Barney Thomson, who works at Henderson's Barbers in Bridgeton and lives a life of desperate mediocrity. Barney's uninteresting life gets turned upside down when he enters the grotesque and comically absurd world of a serial killer after accidentally killing his boss Wullie.","m_cast":"Robert Carlyle as Barney Thomson | Emma Thompson as Cemolina, Barney's mother | Ray Winstone as Hold-all | Ashley Jensen as Detective Inspector June Robertson | Sam Robertson as Detective Sergeant Sam Jobson | Brian Pettifer as Charlie, Barney's friend | Stephen McCole as Wullie Henderson, Barney's boss | Eileen McCallum as Mrs. Gaffney | James Cosmo as James Henderson, Wullie's father and the owner of Henderson's Barbers | Barbara Rafferty as Jean Monkrieff","m_reception":"The Legend of Barney Thomson has received mixed reviews from critics. On Rotten Tomatoes, the film has a rating of 59%, based on 29 reviews, with an average rating of 5.97/10. The site's consensus statement reads, \"The Legend of Barney Thomson may not quite live up to its grandiose title, but it offers a fine calling card for debuting director Carlyle, and Emma Thompson's performance adds a spark.\"[5] On Metacritic, the film has a score of 59 out of 100, based on 9 reviews, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".[6]","m_production":null,"m_sequel":null,"m_based_on":"The Long Midnight of Barney Thomson  by Douglas Lindsay","m_directed_by":"Robert Carlyle","m_produced_by":"John G. Lenic Kaleena Kiff Brian Coffey Holly Brydson Richard Cowan","m_screenplay_by":"Colin McLaren Richard Cowan","m_story_by":null,"m_starring":"Robert Carlyle Emma Thompson Ray Winstone Ashley Jensen Brian Pettifer","m_music_by":null,"m_cinematography":"Fabian Wagner","m_edited_by":null,"m_production_company":null,"m_distributed_by":"Gravitas Ventures","m_release_dates":"17 June 2015 (2015-06-17) (Edinburgh International Film Festival) | 24 July 2015 (2015-07-24) |